Description: Body-sherd of a pale-red pottery wine-jar, exterior covered with a cream slip, with remains of one lines of black-painted hieratic text on the exterior specifying the contents as seremet-liquid.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389874) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389874)
